      "id": 35918,
      "kuerzel": "SFROBOTICS",
      "bezeichnung": "SF-Robotics",
      "lernziele": "<p><strong>Fachkompetenz</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Understand the functions and properties of robots as well as their fields of application</li>\n<li>Evaluate suitable robot technologies for automation tasks</li>\n<li>Understand the advantages and challenges of collaborative robotics compared to standard industrial robots</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Methodenkompetenz</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identify potential applications for using robots in industrial production</li>\n<li>Apply robot technologies to address these applications</li>\n<li>Determine safety, social and economic impacts of a robot solution</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Selbstkompetenz</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Critically review and revise self-developed solutions based on updated requirements</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Sozialkompetenz</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop case studies in teamwork</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "planinhalt": "<p><strong>Introduction to robotics</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Types of industrial robots, overview of applications</li>\n<li>Robot kinematics: Coordinate transformation, workspace</li>\n<li>Robot sensors and vision</li>\n<li>Trajectory planning</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br /><strong>Human Robot Collaboration</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Characteristics and applications of collaborative robots</li>\n<li>Legal framework, safety, economics in collaborative robotic applications</li>\n<li>Use cases</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br /><strong>Lab Exercise</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Hands-on programming of robots</li>\n<li>Simulation of robots in digital factory</li>\n<li>Programming of collaborative robots for an assembly application</li>\n</ul>",
